      sampleAnswer: "Technology has fundamentally transformed the educational landscape over the past two decades. Digital tools such as online learning platforms, interactive whiteboards, and educational applications have made knowledge more accessible than ever before. Students can now access lectures from renowned universities worldwide, participate in virtual laboratories, and collaborate with peers across different continents. However, an over-reliance on technology poses significant risks. Studies indicate that excessive screen time can diminish students' ability to concentrate and engage in deep, critical thinking. Moreover, the digital divide means that not all students have equal access to technological resources, potentially exacerbating existing inequalities. To address these challenges, educators should adopt a blended approach that combines the efficiency of digital tools with the irreplaceable value of face-to-face interaction and hands-on learning experiences. Looking ahead, the future of education will likely involve adaptive learning systems powered by artificial intelligence, which can personalize instruction to meet each student's unique needs while preserving the essential human elements of mentorship and guidance.",
